    //      - remotely with 2 decimals --> 1.23 => uint(123)
    //      - The conversion rate would be 10 ** (4 - 2) = 100
    //  @dev If you want to send 1.2345 -> (uint 12345), you CANNOT represent that value on the remote,
    //  you can only display 1.23 -> uint(123).
